{
  "description": "Express intent in code first, comments second. Rename variables/functions instead of commenting, extract methods to make intent clear, and use comments only when code can't express intent.",
  "scanner": "agile_bot.bots.base_bot.src.scanners.useless_comments_scanner.UselessCommentsScanner",
  "examples": [
    {
      "do": {
        "description": "Express intent through clear code",
        "content": [
          "Rename variables/functions instead of commenting",
          "Extract methods to make intent clear",
          "Use comments only when code can't express intent",
          "Self-documenting code is better than commented code",
          "",
          "Correct Examples (code over comments):",
          "BAD: // check if employee is eligible for benefits",
          "     if (employee.flags && HOURLY_FLAG && employee.age > 65)",
          "",
          "GOOD: if (employee.isEligibleForBenefits())",
          "",
          "BAD: // format as currency",
          "     const result = '$' + value.toFixed(2);",
          "",
          "GOOD: const result = formatAsCurrency(value);",
          "",
          "Code Expression Requirements:",
          "- Clear variable/function names",
          "- Extracted methods for complex logic",
          "- Descriptive names that explain purpose",
          "- Code reads like well-written prose",
          "",
          "When Docstrings/Comments ARE Valuable:",
          "- Test scenarios describing business behavior (GIVEN/WHEN/THEN)",
          "- Public API documentation for external users",
          "- Complex algorithms with non-obvious intent",
          "- Business rules that can't be expressed in code",
          "- Why something is done (not what/how)",
          "- Legal requirements, compliance notes",
          "- Example: SCENARIO: User checkout flow with 3% discount"
        ]
      },
      "dont": {
        "description": "Don't use comments to explain bad code",
        "content": [
          "Don't use comments to explain bad code",
          "Don't add noise comments stating the obvious",
          "Don't let comments become outdated",
          "",
          "Wrong Examples (unnecessary comments):",
          "// set the value",
          "value = 5;",
          "",
          "// loop through users",
          "for (const user of users) {...}",
          "",
          "// constructor",
          "constructor() {...}",
          "",
          "Noise Comment Indicators (DELETE):",
          "- Comments stating what code obviously does",
          "- Default comments from code generators",
          "- Redundant JavaDoc for simple getters/setters",
          "- Comments that just repeat function names",
          "",
          "Instead:",
          "- Improve code to be self-explanatory",
          "- Extract complex logic to named functions",
          "- Use descriptive names instead of comments",
          "- Delete obvious/outdated comments"
        ]
      }
    }
  ]
}

























